ALLIANCE FC top scorer David Richard has said he is ready to leave his club at end of the season. Speaking to the ‘Daily News’ here yesterday, Richard said he is  ready to feature for any side among the Premier League sides, adding he is ready to part ways with his current team. He further added that his current contract will end at the end of this month. However, the former Pamba SC player said he has not received any offer from other Premier League teams, but he now focuses to move to other teams so that he can begin a new life there. Richard disclosed that he is ready to play for any team that may need his services. David has so far featured in 22 league matches, scoring six goals and providing nine assists. He has also netted one hat-trick in their 4-1 win over Mwadui at Nyamagana stadium in Mwanza. He called upon the team's fans and the football fraternity in Mwanza to continue supporting their team in all their remaining matches. Alliance FC, who are struggling to avoid relegation zone, are placed 18th on the league table after gathering 29 points from 29 outings. They have won five, drawn seven and lost 14 matches.He further promised to work hard with his fellow players so as to help their team to win nine remaining matches of the  premier league, which he belives will help their team avoid relegation. At Nyamagana stadium, they will play six consecutive matches against Ndanda FC, Namungo FC, Coastal Union, Police Tanzania, Mtibwa Sugar and Lipuli FC while their away matches will be against JKT Tanzania at Jamhuri stadium, Mbeya City at Sokoine memorial Stadium in Mbeya. Their last league fixture will be at Uhuru stadium in Dar es Salaam whereby the will face defending champions Simba SC.